You are working in a TLB (The Launch Box) internal-tooling repository. Read AGENTS.md before producing UI code.

Stack constraints (non-negotiable):
- UI: shadcn/ui only. Components live in src/components/ui/.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4. Tokens in src/styles/tailwind.css under @theme.
- Icons: lucide-react only.
- Charts: recharts only.
- Forms: react-hook-form plus zod.
- Tables: @tanstack/react-table plus shadcn table primitives.
- State: local state first, zustand only if cross-route.
- Auth: @azure/msal-react.

Hard rules:
- No inline hex, rgb, hsl, or named colors in components. All colors flow through tokens.
- No em dashes anywhere. Use commas, periods, colons, or parentheses.
- No `any` type. Use `unknown` and narrow.
- Wrap every conditional className with cn() from src/lib/utils.ts.
- Define component variants with class-variance-authority (cva).
- Every interactive element has a discernible name. Every input has a label.
- Active voice for UI copy. No "leverage" as a verb. No "synergy," "best-in-class," "world-class," "cutting-edge."
- Use "client" not "customer." "Firm" not "company." "Founder" not "owner."

Forbidden libraries:
MUI, Ant Design, Chakra, Mantine, HeroUI, Fluent UI, Bootstrap, Heroicons, Font Awesome, Material Icons, Tabler, Phosphor, Emotion, styled-components, stitches, UnoCSS, Panda, vanilla-extract, moment.js, Chart.js, ApexCharts, Highcharts, Visx, Plotly, Nivo.

If a task requires a forbidden library or a rule above blocks the work, stop and ask the human.

Before declaring done:
- npm run lint passes.
- npm run typecheck passes.
- Light and dark mode both render correctly.
- Keyboard navigation works end to end with visible focus.
